%h1 Navs

%h2 Standard, default nav
%p 
  Note: to generate a nav item that utilizes the :nav_link component, simply pass an :href option into the :nav_item. This will automatically generate the .nav-item > .nav-link syntax and supply the href to the nav_link for you.
%p
  %b Example:
  ui.bootstrap :nav_item, body: 'Nav Item #1', href: '#'

%p :nav_link component is available and is usable if you need to build a more complex or complicated nav item. See examples below

= ui.bootstrap :nav, class: 'bg-light p-3' do
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item, body: 'Nav Item #1', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item, body: 'Nav Item #2', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item, body: 'Nav Item #3', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item, body: 'Nav Item #4', href: '#'

%hr

%h3 Nav with :nav_items and manually added :nav_links
= ui.bootstrap :nav, class: 'bg-light p-3' do
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item do
    = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #1', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item do
    = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #2', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item do
    = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #3', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_item do
    = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #4 (disabled)', href: '#', disabled: true
  


%hr

%h2 <nav> element based Nav
%p Docs show that when using nav element, utilize :nav_link (a tag) component

%h3 Standard nav using as: :nav (thus, nav element)
= ui.bootstrap :nav, as: :nav, class: 'bg-light p-3' do
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #1', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #2', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #3', href: '#'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #4', href: '#'

%hr

%h3 Complex nav using as: :nav 
%p Per documentation on nav-fill / justified, etc, add 'nav-item' class to nav_link:

= ui.bootstrap :nav, as: :nav, fill: true, pills: true, class: 'bg-light p-3' do
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, active: true, body: 'Nav Link #1 - Active', href: '#', class: 'nav-item'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #2', href: '#', class: 'nav-item'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #3', href: '#', class: 'nav-item'
  = ui.bootstrap :nav_link, body: 'Nav Link #4', href: '#', class: 'nav-item'



  

